name: 1890 townhome in popular LoHi! 2018-BFN-0009355
description: Perfect space/location for longer term visitors. Cozy townhome within walking distance to best neighborhood in Denver. Stay in a fully equipped home, ready for grilling in the backyard or heading out to amazing local restaurants.
neighborhood_overview: LoHi is one of the fastest growing, hottest neighborhoods not just in Denver, but in the country. The neighborhood has several of the highest rated restaurants in Denver, and is walkable to other neighborhoods as well, including Platte Street, Union Station/LoDo, RiNo and the Highlands. Much of the neighborhood feels very residential, yet you can be at a great watering hole, coffee shop or restaurant within just a few minutes' walk.
host_about:
I have been lucky to have traveled extensively, volunteered worldwide and because where you lay your head at night can be such an impactful part of your travels, I'm always looking for opportunities to create a welcoming and comfortable place, whether you are vacationing, stopping on your way through or working remotely.   

I grew up in the Midwest, lived in Chicago for several years, and now love the mountains as much as I love all my favorite destinations, from cities (San Francisco, Chicago, London) to mountain towns (Aspen, Crested Butte and Telluride) to international bucket list destinations (Mt. Kilimanjaro, Mombasa, Marrakesh).

I believe that travel is the key to understanding different people and different cultures, and I have learned that people are fabulous all over the world! 

Our goal is to make your experience feel tranquil, rejuvenating and special. Like you're home (but not!)  Feel free to follow me on IG: @vjarstad and on FB: Valerie Jarstad.

name: Cozy Eastbridge Home walk to everything!
description: This new home is bright, light and open with all the modern conveniences. There is a brand new shopping/dining area just 4 blocks from the house with a high end King Soopers and three of the newly named "Top 25" Restaurants in the Denver area. It's just 20 minutes from downtown and the airport and surrounded by parks, trails, swimming pools, a rec. center, shopping and great restaurants. The new Stanley Marketplace is just over a mile away!
neighborhood_overview:
Just across the street, we have Bluff Lake Nature Center. Early morning walks (there is a mile dirt path around it (no bikes)) are awesome. There are beautiful birds everywhere, deer, foxes, even bald eagles in the winter. The Sand Creek trail heads NW and SE from there and you can connect it with trails to go all around the city of denver.
About 4 blocks west is one of our neighborhood's pools. You will have to buy a day pass. This summer, there will be 5 pools to chose from in the hood. A half mile from the house is the Central Park Recreation Center with a large indoor pool and workout room and cardio equipment that looks out over Stapelton's Central Park and west to the mountains. There are bike/walking trails everywhere and a 2 1/2 mile walk/ride takes you to our town center with restaurants, groceries, bars, etc. I can get downton in 15 minutes on Martin Luther King Blvd and the same to the airport via 1-70. Stapleton is a fantastic location to see all that Denver has to off
host_about:
I have been living in Denver for the past ten years. After growing up outside of Philadelphia, spending 8 years in Maine and living all over the west (MT, AK, ID), Denver has become a great place to call home. The Stapleton community is a great balance between city and suburbs. We have great restaurants and trails for biking, walking and running are everywhere. The sand creek trail is right across the street from my house and you can run, walk, bike all the way downtown to REI and beyond on it. 
I love the outdoors and Denver is very conducive to an outdoor focused lifestyle. I spend half of my time in a tiny town of 450 people in Creede, Colorado. I enjoy running and mountain biking the trails around Creede as well as floating on the Rio Grande River.

name: Mid-Century Modern Room - Minutes to Cherry Creek
description: Welcome! My home is a mid-century modern, open plan that is just a few minutes away from light-rail, and Cherry Creek. It's very easy to access I-25 and go either to the Tech Center or Downtown if you're driving. No matter your background, all are welcome.
neighborhood_overview: I'm sandwiched between two mid-century modern housing developments. To the north is "Krisana Park"... A mid-century enclave that is fondly referred to as "Leichler" since it thinks it is "like Eichler". To the east is "Lynwood"... Very similar houses and very much in demand. This house was built in 1958 and is one of a kind. Other stuff? We have an authentic french bakery two blocks away (Detour) as well as an independent coffee house: Sojourners. The bus route begins a block away. The Lightrail "Colorado Station" is a mile's walk and can take you either south to the Tech Center, east to DIA or north to Downtown Denver. Cherry Creek is about 10 mins by car and has great shopping, restaurants and movie theaters. If you love gourmet, niche pizza, we have a fantastic neighborhood bistro, "Esters" that opened about a year ago. Their nachos are mouth-watering. They have a few awesome salads, some sandwiches and of course, what most people go for... The pizza (and the craft beers). Think aru
host_about: I've lived in the USA for 30+ years after narrowly escaping a rainy future in England. I can discuss American politics but not English ones, unless you count the politics of the school playground. I love chess. I've won one lottery (although there was no cash involved, just an elusive Green Card). I play six-degrees-of-separation for fun and find that in Denver, it's usually only two or three degrees (even if it's the President or a Hollywood movie star and sometimes it's one and the same). I am completely in love with my dog, Bodhi (a non-shedding, Portuguese Water Dog), who lives up to his name in every way (a being of wisdom and enlightenment). I am bummed (how's that for eloquence) that neither DaVinci or Einstein are still anchored to Terra Firma because I'd love to meet them, sit around a fountain somewhere (hopefully with an Americano in hand) and ask them what their take is on "Life, The Universe and Everything"... (Thank you Douglas Adams.) I love "Game of Thrones", "Homeland" and all things "Shameless"... And I'm just a little obsessed with the whole mid-century modern thing.

Just a few minutes walk to the vibrant Old South Pearl street district and one block from the park!

name: Updated & Cozy Denver Bungalow
description: Minutes from Downtown Denver, RINO, LoDo and the Highlands, this cozy 3 bedroom bungalow in Denver's Chaffee Park neighborhood is close to everything! Conveniently located with access to I-70 & I-25 our home is great for Denver-area stays and makes for SUPER EASY access to the I-70 corridor for mountain day trips and getaways.
neighborhood_overview: The Chaffee Park neighborhood is a quiet Denver neighborhood that is beginning to emerge. Most residents in this area have lived here for 20+ years. There is a large concrete tower located to the northeast of the home. While it may look like an imposing structure, rest assured that it's harmless. The tower houses legacy microwave equipment that was in use from the mid-1960's to the mid-1970's. The tower was part of a nationwide network that was effectively an early incarnation of the internet. Since going out of service in the mid-1970's, the equipment has been deactivated and the space is currently vacant and not in use.
host_about: My name is Jason. I enjoy baseball by  summer, hockey by winter and there’s only one place that you’ll find me on the first Saturday in May! I once made a living making whiskey; I’ve driven a Zamboni; I like to build things; and my goal in life is to give back. My go-to cocktail is a properly made sazerac cocktail and rarely will I turn down a properly made black manhattan. My beer of choice is an ice cold Coors Banquet after a long day of work. I enjoy hosting and getting the opportunity to meet some truly wonderful people along the way!

name: 5 BIG bdrms/huge yard, quiet, central Denver oasis
description: Serene, spacious exterior/interior; chosen locale for Emmys-nom'd production co's on-site film, small weddings, showers. BEST PRICE for size/location: 2800sf w/5 BIG bdrms/7500 lot w/mature landscape, romantic vine-covered pergola w/gas firepit, quiet/historic 'hood. French doors to BIG suite; 5-pc granite bath/walk-in closet; LUXE details: stained glass/Turkish wool rugs/real alabaster lamps/2 cozygas fireplaces/2 patios/3 outdoor tables/many chairs/grill/coffeebar/designer cotton sheets/towels
neighborhood_overview: ELEGANT & HISTORIC, MONTCLAIR --  Denver's  Montclair neighborhood is lined with brick homes, tree-lined avenues, and eccentric local businesses. Montclair is the brainchild of Baron Walter von Richthofen, a Prussian aristocrat and the uncle of famed WWI German pilot "Red Baron" Manfred von Richthofen who wanted an "utopian community" built on what were at the time empty fields east of Denver.  He started in 1887 with building what is now known as the community's centerpiece, the 14,938-square-foot limestone Richthofen Castle, located at 7020 E. 12th Ave.  My husband and I feel lucky to live here in Montclair with its beautiful homes and quiet and peaceful neighborhood, but we acknowledge that our "Utopia" has to evolve to include all souls.
host_about:
Susan and Tim both worked in the world of water in Colorado. Susan was an attorney working to protect the natural environment and Tim was an engineer working on water projects to enhance and maintain the beauty of Colorado.

Susan is a proud member of the Cheyenne River Sioux tribe. We welcome diversity and inclusion. We hope to welcome you!

We live here, so please understand that when you book with us, we book a rental about an hour and a half away, but can respond quickly by text or call to questions.

name: Custom Modern Luxury Denver Home Rooftop City View
description: Nestled in central Denver, our newly constructed modern residence has 4 bedrooms and 4.5 bathrooms. The house is unmatched in proximity to the city’s premier destinations: Red Rocks Amphitheater, Mile High Stadium, Ball Arena, Coors Field, and Meow Wolf!  Enjoy breathtaking city views from the furnished patio featuring a fire pit. Revel in elegance with a state-of-the-art kitchen, an indoor fireplace, a fully furnished basement, and expansive windows that bathe the interior in natural light.
neighborhood_overview:
Enjoy the outdoors and explore Denver's vibrant downtown with ease!

Ride bikes into downtown Denver using the picturesque Lakewood Gulch Bike Path and immerse yourself in the city's lively atmosphere.

Or, if you're looking for a more leisurely activity, grab a frisbee and head to Dry Gulch Park for a game of frisbee golf

For a quick and convenient way to get downtown, hop on the Perry Street Light Rail, which is just a five-minute walk away.

Once in downtown Denver, you'll be within walking distance of iconic attractions like Mile High Stadium and the captivating Meow Wolf art museum.

Don't miss out on this opportunity to experience the best of Denver in a fun and active way by staying at my home!
host_about:
Hello, I'm Jason! I've called Colorado home since 1995, originally hailing from Chile. I'm passionate about the outdoors and all the amazing activities Colorado has to offer. Whether you're into snowboarding, mountain/gravel/dirt biking, rafting, skateboarding, or just exploring with your dog, I'm here to share recommendations to make your Denver stay perfect.

My motto is:
"You can't stop the waves, but you can learn how to surf."

description: This private cozy guest suite with separate entrance is the perfect spot for solo travelers, couples, or friends looking to explore Colorado. Located just a half block from City Park, and within walking distance to the Denver Zoo, Museum of Nature and Science, and Botanical Gardens! Downtown is just 2 miles away and Red Rocks Amphitheater is only 30 minutes away. We provide all the essentials for a comfortable stay. So come enjoy all that Colorado has to offer with our home away from home!
neighborhood_overview:
Our house is located in a quiet residential neighborhood adjacent to what is arguably Denver’s best park, the 314-acre City Park. Here you’ll find the Denver Zoo, 14 tennis courts, a lake with boat rentals, the Denver Museum of Nature & Science, Jazz in the Park (on summer Sundays) and the newly renovated 18-hole City Park golf course. The Denver Botanical Gardens is located just over a mile away.

Houses, from slightly weathered Victorians to newer condos, are peppered throughout the neighborhood. A large portion of City Park West’s north end is taken up by hospitals and medical centers; to the south, East 17th and East Colfax avenues are busy commercial corridors that draw people of all ages to their buzzing blocks.
host_about: My wife Shannon and I live in Denver with our golden retriever Oakley. We enjoy hiking and exploring the City and love designing spaces that give our guests a comfortable landing spot for their own adventures!

Five Points is the perfect home base for exploring Denver and the Front Range. This neighborhood is well known among Mile High locals for its walkability and historical significance. You’ll find coffee shops, craft breweries, museums, and independent music venues outside your door. Soak up the tasteful and vibrant blend of old and new establishments while exploring Denver’s historic landmarks and longstanding food institutions.

description: If you are in town for a conference at the convention center, this is the place to book! Welcome to your dream getaway in Denver's historic Santa Fe Arts District, where you'll discover the perfect blend of local luxury and Rocky Mountain vibes. neighborhood_overview:
Welcome to your dream getaway in the heart of Denver's historic Santa Fe Arts District, where you'll discover the perfect blend of modern luxury and Rocky Mountain vibes. We're excited to introduce you to this exceptional property and the vibrant neighborhood it calls home.

La Alma Lincoln Park is not only one of Denver’s oldest residential neighborhoods, with a rare concentration of homes built before 1890, but it was also at the heart of Denver’s Chicano Movement, or El Movimiento, in the 1960s and 1970s. The neighborhood demonstrates the close connection between place and people, made tangible by the surviving structures set close together — diverse in their architectural styles yet maintaining a consistent pattern for 150 years. We invite you to explore the streets of your historic neighborhood.

name: Berkeley Bungalow: Indoor Outdoor Living, Mtn View
description: Welcome to the Berkeley Bungalow! Savor indoor-outdoor living with a mountain view in a charming, safe, walkable neighborhood near Tennyson St. This isn't your cookie-cutter Airbnb—it's my cherished home, infused with personality and warmth. Natural light floods the southwestern-boho styled space, creating a peaceful sanctuary. Conveniently located on a bike street and near I-70/25, adventure awaits—whether you're heading to the mountains or exploring the city, easily enjoy the best of CO!
host_about: I love the outdoors, especially exploring the mountains with my 10lb adventure pup! I am all about finding a “basecamp” to call home when traveling so that I can get to know a place more deeply, and I hope that my bungalow can be that for you! I am a first time homeowner and feel so lucky to have found the beautiful home that I did and am excited to share it with others while I take a sabbatical leading backpacking trips in the Rockies!
